scription":"Maven users who want to test their Java projects against different JDKs often do so by re-running their Maven build with each such JDK. Maven's Toolchains plugin offers an alternative strategy for testing across JDKs.\n"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/maven-toolchain-tests/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/owasp-xxe-jaxb/","sourceName":"blog"},"frontmatter":{"title":"üîí XML External Entity Pitfalls With JAXB"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blog/stream-stax/","sourceName":"blog"},"frontmatter":{"title":"‚òïÔ∏è Connecting Java's Streaming API for XML (StAX) with Streams"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383","614056702"],"slicesMap":{}}